# Consumer App Visual Reference

When asked to verify, test, or fix app appearance, use this as the authoritative reference for how each app should look.

## Shared Visual Elements (All Apps)

Every DedgeAuth-integrated consumer app must have:

- **FK Green header/branding**: `#008942` gradient from tenant CSS
- **Dedge logo**: Loaded from DedgeAuth tenant logo endpoint (not local files)
- **DedgeAuth user menu**: `<div id="DedgeAuthUserMenu"></div>` — top-right dropdown with user info, app switcher, logout
- **Tenant CSS injection**: `<style id="DedgeAuth-tenant-css">` populated dynamically by `DedgeAuth-user.js`
- **Dark/light theme toggle**: Where applicable

### CSS Load Order

1. App's own local CSS (`css/site.css` or similar)
2. DedgeAuth common CSS (`api/DedgeAuth/ui/common.css` via proxy)
3. Tenant-specific CSS (injected into `#DedgeAuth-tenant-css` by `user.js`)
4. DedgeAuth user menu CSS (`api/DedgeAuth/ui/user.css` via proxy)

