## Visual Verification Checklist

When verifying any consumer app visually, confirm ALL of these:

- [ ] FK Green branding visible (not unstyled/default Bootstrap)
- [ ] Dedge logo displayed (not broken image)
- [ ] DedgeAuth user menu present and functional (dropdown opens, shows user info)
- [ ] App switcher in user menu lists other apps
- [ ] Tenant CSS applied (check `#DedgeAuth-tenant-css` has content)
- [ ] No JavaScript console errors related to DedgeAuth
- [ ] Theme toggle works (if present)
- [ ] Navigation links work (use `~/` paths, not `/` absolute paths in IIS virtual apps)

## Common Visual Issues

| Symptom | Likely Cause |
|---------|-------------|
| Completely unstyled page | `DedgeAuth-user.js` not loading tenant CSS — check proxy endpoint and `DedgeAuthUrl` |
| Missing user menu | No `<div id="DedgeAuthUserMenu">` in HTML, or `user.js` not loaded |
| Broken logo | Tenant has no `logo_data` in DB, or logo endpoint returning 404 |
| White/default header | Tenant CSS not injected — check `#DedgeAuth-tenant-css` element is empty |
| Links go to wrong app | Absolute paths (`/page`) instead of virtual-app-relative (`~/page`) |
